The paper deals with the detection of cyber-attacks on state estimation in power systems. This topic falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and system control (cs.SY). The proposed approach involves the use of multiple metrics and a two-stage detection process, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and network infrastructure (cs.NI) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of false data injection on the system, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE).
